        The list of message attachments

      • availability

        public java.lang.String availability
        Message availability status. Message in 'Deleted' state is still preserved with all its attachments and can be restored. 'Purged' means that all attachments are already deleted and the message itself is about to be physically deleted shortly Enum: Alive, Deleted, Purged

      • conversationId

        public java.lang.Long conversationId
        SMS and Pager only. Identifier of a conversation the message belongs to Format: int64

      • conversation

        public ConversationInfo conversation

      • creationTime

        public java.lang.String creationTime
        Message creation datetime in ISO 8601 format including timezone, for example 2016-03-10T18:07:52.534Z Format: date-time

      • deliveryErrorCode

        public java.lang.String deliveryErrorCode
        SMS only. Delivery error code returned by gateway

      • direction

        public java.lang.String direction
        Message direction. Note that for some message types not all directions are allowed. For example voicemail messages can be only inbound Enum: Inbound, Outbound

      • faxPageCount

        public java.lang.Long faxPageCount
        Fax only. Page count in a fax message

      • faxResolution

        public java.lang.String faxResolution
        Fax only. Resolution of a fax message. 'High' for black and white image scanned at 200 dpi, 'Low' for black and white image scanned at 100 dpi Enum: High, Low

      • from

        public MessageSenderInfo from

      • lastModifiedTime

        public java.lang.String lastModifiedTime
        The datetime when the message was modified on server in ISO 8601 format including timezone, for example 2016-03-10T18:07:52.534Z Format: date-time

      • messageStatus

        public java.lang.String messageStatus
        Message status. Different message types may have different allowed status values.For outbound faxes the aggregated message status is returned: If status for at least one recipient is 'Queued', then 'Queued' value is returned If status for at least one recipient is 'SendingFailed', then 'SendingFailed' value is returned In other cases Sent status is returned Enum: Queued, Sent, Delivered, DeliveryFailed, SendingFailed, Received

      • pgToDepartment

        public java.lang.Boolean pgToDepartment
        'Pager' only. 'True' if at least one of the message recipients is 'Department' extension

      • priority

        public java.lang.String priority
        Message priority Enum: Normal, High

      • readStatus

        public java.lang.String readStatus
        Message read status Enum: Read, Unread

      • smsDeliveryTime

        public java.lang.String smsDeliveryTime
        SMS only. The datetime when outbound SMS was delivered to recipient's handset in ISO 8601 format including timezone, for example 2016-03-10T18:07:52.534Z. It is filled only if the carrier sends a delivery receipt to RingCentral Format: date-time

      • smsSendingAttemptsCount

        public java.lang.Long smsSendingAttemptsCount
        SMS only. Number of attempts made to send an outbound SMS to the gateway (if gateway is temporary unavailable)

      • subject

        public java.lang.String subject
        Message subject. For SMS and Pager messages it replicates message text which is also returned as an attachment

      • to

        public MessageRecipientInfo[] to
        Recipient information

      • type

        public java.lang.String type
        Message type Enum: Fax, SMS, VoiceMail, Pager, Text

      • vmTranscriptionStatus

        public java.lang.String vmTranscriptionStatus
        Voicemail only. Status of voicemail to text transcription. If VoicemailToText feature is not activated for account, the 'NotAvailable' value is returned Enum: NotAvailable, InProgress, TimedOut, Completed, CompletedPartially, Failed
